Be that as it may, Mayong Mistmoore and his agents are my enemy.  Thrads is the unliving embodiment of Mayong's will, therefore this chance to weaken that House should be taken.  Mayong can unleash a plague of vampires and other agents upon the world.  Witness his vampires, his lesser undead, his semi-spider drachnids in Kunark, and his agents in other places.<br>
<br>
Surely the League of Antonican Bards will choose to fight against Mayong.  Surely those aligned with the Ring of Scale would choose to fight against Mayong.<br>
<br>
Gore is mortal, no matter what flaws he may have.  I don't see League of Honor or the League of Shadows bending to his will anytime soon.  Lord Mayong is a god in all but name, and I know of no oaths by which he can be bound, and who alone amongst us is strong enough to stand up to him, let alone his primary agent in Thrads.<br>
<br>
Evil and good have nothing to do with it.  Honor and loyalty have nothing to do it.  Both are evil, both have folk who respect and honor them.  So what.  <br>
<br>
I will be there fighting against Thrads. <br>
